# Final Project Proposal

## Project Title
Fake News Detection using Deep Learning

---

## Problem Statement
The goal of this project is to build a model that can classify news articles as fake or real.

This problem is important because misinformation spreads quickly online and can influence public opinion. Detecting fake news automatically can help platforms and users identify unreliable information.

The model will take a news article (text) as input and predict whether it is:

- Fake
- Real

---

## Dataset
**Name:** Fake and Real News Dataset  
**Source:** https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/clmentbisaillon/fake-and-real-news-dataset  

### Description
- ~45,000 news articles
- Two classes: fake and real

### Features
- title – headline of the article
- text – main content
- subject – topic
- date – publication date

### Target
- label (0 = fake, 1 = real)

### Format
CSV files

---

## Planned Method

### Baseline Model
- Logistic Regression
- TF-IDF vectorization

### Deep Learning Model
- LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory)

### Optional Improvement
- BERT (pretrained transformer model)

### Training Setup
- Loss Function: CrossEntropyLoss
- Optimizer: Adam

### Evaluation Metrics
- Accuracy
- F1-score

### Data Split
- Train: 70%
- Validation: 15%
- Test: 15%

---

## Expected Challenges
- Long text sequences
- Noisy or inconsistent data
- Class imbalance
- Overfitting
- Computational limitations (training time)

